ers. After looking around the science clubs at Yahoo I was disapointed to discover that most only daydreamed about futuristic technologies. Even the biggest clubs dismissed nuclear power out of hand. So I started my own little club dedicated to the most remarkable nuclear engine ever concieved of. A couple of people would briefly pass through. Out of curiosity mostly. Then Bestonnet arrived and he must have told a few friends about the place shortly after that because it began to grow. At around the same time I discovered an invitation tool and started going around the other clubs typing usernames into the invitation auto sender. One at a time they went out and gradually the membership rose and some interesting topics began forming. Things like NERVA, Super Orions, Nuclear Salt Water Rockets, various political barriers, Science Fiction Stories from Pournelle and Sagan etc etc etc etc. We were fast catching up with the top clubs in membership size and they must have begun to notice. I never went over to any other club myself. I was far too absorbed in trying to comprehend the incredible threads appearing at my own board. <br>
<br>
Then one day a couple of members said that the top club was bagging us. They were posting all kinds of lies about us. I went over there and saw them writing things like we believed a single nuclear bomb could put a manned ship into space. There was a whole list of stupid posts like that by the founders and some were very insulting to us. I corrected the mistakes in responses and was turned on. I had never encountered anything like it before. They would delete my replies for showing them up and then say I obviously knew nothing and couldn't answer their questions. I was amazed. I was also banned, so I couldn't refute the claims either. Out of embarassment, I think, they began a smear campaign. I threatened to report them to Yahoo and was told &quot;Yahoo didn't give a rats arse about complaints.&quot; I soon discovered this to be true. I went as far as individually emailing the members of the ASTS club and explaining the situation so that they wouldn't believe all the lies being perpetrated. That we were con artists, criminals, black, asian, transexual, pedophile, homo etc etc. That they actually considered being called black or asian an insult only demonstrated they were also clearly racist. Something I detest. I myself am a happily married white male but I could easily have been asian or black. In the end things just became impossible. Returning to the easy flow of conversation we had once enjoyed  at the club so seemingly long ago just wasn't concievable. Other clubs were sending us warnings of ASTS badmouthing us at other boards and on top of attacks directed at our own board it just became too much. Hundreds of reports to Yahoo had resulted in only autoreplies. We had to take action. The founders of ASTS were always fighting with somebody I had discovered. Before us it had been other clubs. They even attacked their own members and each other quite frequently. Anybody who disagreed with them was booted out. Using misinformation to take advantage of a fight going on between the founders, &quot;persons unknown&quot; tricked Cerulian Freight into granting founder status to them. They then had a ball deleting everything in sight. The chief nutcase Canada2902 arrived and tried to distract them with obscenities while he furiously pleaded to Yahoo for help. He had forgotten that &quot;Yahoo doesn't give a rats arse about complaints.&quot;<br>
<br>
