God!<br>
Lets see - I entered the fray well after ASTS had been deleted. PO invited me to the club, and I became intrigued. I argued with founders (I accused one of being a bit high-handed and arrogant), and in general had a good time. This was the first time I became aware of “Project: Orion” and I was fascinated.<br>
<br>
Shortly thereafter, I witnessed a massive disruption of the club. A small group of bored morons decided it would be a jolly blast to post obscenities, lies, and in general make things unpleasant. They made accusations that Club founders were disrupting various clubs, and posted hundreds of messages at a time. <br>
<br>
Being the curious outsider I am, I began to investigate their claims. I even went so far as to create a separate club and give them the opportunity to present their case. I was accused of being a toady and a spy, and they warned their cohorts to avoid me. I joined one of their public clubs, and was promptly banned (Unlike them, I never tried to conceal who I was. I didn’t use sub-identities or separate id’s to obfuscate myself.)  – even though I hadn’t posted a thing at their insipid little club.<br>
<br>
Somewhere in here, Orion made me a founder. To this day I am amazed that he did this – as a founder I could have deleted the club, and my actions could easily have been those of someone seeking to gain confidence for nefarious purposes. I had even advised against make any more founders, just in case someone was posing friendly. <br>
<br>
Well, I was now enlisted. I deleted thousands of profanity littered and blank posts (they tended to come in waves). YaHell wouldn’t let you ban people in their clubs unless they were members, and the trolls took advantage of this glitch by joining, posting a storm of crud, and retiring before we could catch them. They would use one-shot names to try and make it seem they were legion. At one point I even phoned Yahell and asked for help – which they promptly refused to provide.<br>
<br>
I learned from this. Orion had allowed his true name and identity to be known, and these gits harasses him. They supposedly called the police, and I believe he did tell me they contacted a former employer and tried to smear his name. I have always been a bit paranoid, but this reinforced my belief in maintaining my anonymity. Even Orion doesn’t know my true name or location – though I am sure they have a good idea of at least where I am (tracking IP addresses had probably revealed my Point of Origin).  <br>
<br>
Now we are here, thank god. I can be just a jackass poster again, and I can sit back and dream of what could have been, and god willing what may be.<br>
